    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the Upper Paleolithic tool-making culture that is contemporaneous with the Aurignacian culture and is concentrated in eastern Europe. It is characterized by burins, borers, leaf-shaped points, Levallois flakes, side scrapers, and end scrapers.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Se refiere a la cultura de fabricación de herramientas Paleolítica Superior que es contemporánea a la cultura Auriñacense y que se concentra en Europa oriental. Se caracteriza por buriles, perforadores, puntas en forma de hoja, lascas Levallois, raspadores laterales, y raspadores de punta.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar de werktuigproducerende cultuur uit het Laat-Paleolithicum, die zich ten tijde van de Aurignac cultuur concentreerde in Oost-Europa. De cultuur kenmerkt zich door naalden, boorders, bladvormige punten, Levallois scherven, randschrabbers en kopschrabbers.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>是指與歐里納克（Aurignacian）文化同一時期的舊石器時代晚期工具製造文化。此文化的特徵是雕刻刀、穿孔器、呈葉片尖狀的尖器、拉瓦洛席安式石片、邊刃刮削器，以及末端 刃刮削器。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
